title: Top of Windmill, Rotterdam
medium: Graphite on cream paperboard tipped into binding with fabric
description: Vertical sheet depicting conical masonry tower pierced at intervals by small rectangular window openings, surmounted by a four-armed wood structure meant to catch the wind.  This structure moves on a central pivot that seems to anchor to the back of the structure.  Below the arms is a walkway that encircles the tower and is visibly supported by timber buttresses from underneath.
name: Album page
